<plot>Young William Bonney inspires the faith and friendship of Pat Garrett, despite Bonney's violent past. Garrett believes that Billy can make a better life for himself, a sentiment shared by rancher John Tunstall, who befriends Billy and gives him a job. Billy falls in love with Tunstall's niece Nita, but this outrages Tunstall's foreman Bob Ollinger, who exposes Billy's past as outlaw Billy the Kid. When one of Billy's new friends is killed, he goes on a rampage of revenge, and Pat Garrett, now a lawman, is forced to go after his young friend.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?570262</url></doc>
